pageContext.claim: “You know, her husband said she was going to lose. Her husband's a professional. Her husband said, 'You know, you better go to Michigan.' Because I was there, and they had Trump-Pence sign on every lawn I've ever seen. 'And you better go to Wisconsin, Hillary. You better go to Wisconsin.' She said, 'No, we haven't lost in Wisconsin in 36 years.' 'No, no. Hillary, you got to go there I'm telling you. I don't like what I saw.' 'No. What do you know?' You know, he's a professional politician. She wasn't.”
pageContext.analysis: Hillary Clinton is a former U.S. Senator, which certainly qualifies her as a “professional politician.” Moreover, it’s incredibly unlikely that Trump would have knowledge of a private conversation between the Clintons.
